      • addOrUpdateAlbumContest

        public AlbumContestResponse addOrUpdateAlbumContest(Long accountId,
                                           String appKey,
                                           String contestType,
                                           Long albumContestId,
                                           String title,
                                           String description,
                                           Long albumId1,
                                           Boolean removeAlbum1,
                                           Long albumId2,
                                           Boolean removeAlbum2,
                                           Long startDate,
                                           Long endDate,
                                           Boolean publicRead,
                                           Boolean publicWrite,
                                           Boolean publicDelete,
                                           Boolean publicAdd,
                                           String locationDescription,
                                           Enums.Visibility visibility,
                                           List<Long> connectionIdsToAdd,
                                           List<Long> connectionGroupIdsToAdd,
                                           Boolean includeFriendGroup,
                                           Location location)
                                             throws SirqulException
        Creates or updates an album contest.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/contest
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user
        appKey - the application key. Maps to "gameType".
        contestType - a custom field used for aggregation and searching
        albumContestId - the album contest ID for updating (don't pass in if creating)
        title - the title of the contest
        description - the description of the contest
        albumId1 - the album ID for the first album
        removeAlbum1 - removes album1 from the contest
        albumId2 - the album ID for the second album
        removeAlbum2 - removes album2 from the contest
        startDate - the start date of the contest (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        endDate - the end date of the contest (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        publicRead - determines whether the contest's participants has read permissions
        publicWrite - determines whether the contest's participants has write permissions
        publicDelete - determines whether the contest's participants has delete permissions
        publicAdd - determines whether the contest's participants has add permissions
        locationDescription - the location description of the contest taking place
        visibility - the determines the album's participants ( Enums.Visibility .PUBLIC - includes everyone in the system as a potential participant, Enums.Visibility.PRIVATE - only considers people who have been invited as participants)
        connectionIdsToAdd - list of connection IDs
        connectionGroupIdsToAdd - list of connection group IDs
        includeFriendGroup - determines whether to include all friends as participants
        location - location used to update the user's current location
        Returns:
        AlbumContestResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • approveAlbumContest

        public SirqulResponse approveAlbumContest(Long accountId,
                                 Long albumContestId,
                                 Enums.ApprovalStatus approvalStatus)
                                   throws SirqulException
        Sets the approval status of an album contest. Only an approval status of APPROVED or FEATURED will be returned when searching for public content. Only someone with EXECUTIVE rights or rights to edit the application can approve/feature the content.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/contest/approve
        Parameters:
        accountId - The account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, device id sent automatically)
        albumContestId - The ID of the album contest
        approvalStatus - The approval status to set {PENDING, REJECTED, APPROVED, FEATURED}
        Returns:
        SirqulResponse with success or fail message.
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • searchAlbumContests

        public AlbumContestListResponse searchAlbumContests(Long accountId,
                                           String appKey,
                                           String appType,
                                           String contestType,

                                           Long dateCreated,
                                           Location location)
                                             throws SirqulException
        Gets or searches on contests.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/contest/search
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user
        appKey - the application key.
        appType - The application type.
        contestType - filter contests with this contest type
        ownerId - search on contests that have been created by this account (that the user has permissions to)
        keyword - keyword search string
        filters - list of Enums.Ownership
        sortField - the field to sort by. See Enums.AlbumContestApiMap
        descending - determines whether the sorted list is in descending or ascending order
        start - the start index for pagination
        limit - the limit for pagination
        dateCreated - filter on items that have been created before this date
        location - location used to update the user's current location
        Returns:
        AlbumContestListResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.
